Dow flat despite losses in Home Depot, Chevron shares

Behind negative returns for shares of Home Depot and Chevron, the Dow Jones Industrial Average is declining Wednesday afternoon. Shares of Home Depot HD, -2.45% and Chevron CVX, -2.24% have contributed to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, -2.29% was most recently trading 7 points (0.0%) lower. Home Depot's shares have declined $3.87, or 1.8%, while those of Chevron have dropped $1.45 (1.2%), combining for a roughly 36-point drag on the Dow. Travelers TRV, -3.51%, Walgreens Boots WBA, -2.18%, and Pfizer PFE, -0.68% are also contributing significantly to the decline. A $1 move in any of the index's 30 components results in a 6.78-point swing.